radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal bibasilar atelectasis; simple free fluid within the pelvis; a tubular blind ending structure demonstrating hyperenhancement and measuring 11 mm in diameter consistent with an inflamed appendix; numerous phleboliths; hyperdense left ovarian cyst previously characterized as hemorrhagic; no pleural or pericardial effusion; normal appearance of liver, gallbladder, pancreas, adrenals, spleen, kidneys, uterus, and adnexa.
